<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   MOFTEC Announces New Border Trade Regulations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0702024094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0526 GMT 
5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0702024094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 5 (CNS)--China's new regulations 
for border trade formulated by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and 
Economic Cooperation [MOFTEC] mainly include the following: 
  Companies engaging in small-volume border trade are subject 
to approval by the ministry regarding their setting up and 
trading sites set up by residents of border areas at border 
trade fairs will be organized in a unified way and managed by 
provincial governments. 
  Before the end of 1995, those companies approved by the 
ministry will have their import tariff and product tax reduced 
by 50 percent on some of their traded commodities (except for 
electro-mechanical products, cigarettes, wines and cosmetics). 
Products worth less than RMB 300 [renminbi] will have taxes 
imposed on them according to regulations while those products 
such as cigarettes, wines and cosmetics will all have taxes 
levied on them. 
  Border trade companies are allowed to export a small amount 
of commodities listed as Category Two and Category Three within 
the total quotas granted by the ministry. 
  Items for cooperation between the border areas and their 
corresponding areas in foreign countries are subject to approval 
by the department in charge of foreign trade and economy under 
the provincial government and commodities (except for 
electro-mechanical products, cigarettes, wines and cosmetics) 
imported through such cooperation and used for the payment to 
laborers on the Chinese side will not have any import tariff and 
product tax levied on them while those other than for this 
purpose will have their taxes reduced by 50 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-26581 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi027_n_94023" </HT>


