<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangxi Government Discusses Government Work Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0902005994 Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0902005994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, the provincial government held a 
plenary meeting to discuss the government work report to be 
submitted to the Second Session of the Eighth Jiangxi Provincial 
People's Congress. Present at the meeting were Wu Guanzheng, Shu 
Shengyou, Huang Zhiquan, Zhou Zhiping, Zhang Yunchuan, Wang 
Maoheng, and Jiang Zhongping. Members of the provincial 
government and principal leaders of the relevant government 
departments also attended the meeting. Governor Wu Guanzheng 
chaired the meeting, which discussed and revised the government 
work, and reviewed last year's achievements. 
  The report points out: The past year has been one in which 
the province maintained speedy national economic growth, in 
which major progress was made in reform, in which the people's 
lives continued to improve, and in which new progress was made 
in building the material and spiritual civilizations. Last 
year, the province's GNP amounted to 68.6 billion yuan, an 
increase of 15.8 percent over the previous year. Gross 
industrial and agricultural output value amounted to 122.1 
billion yuan, an increase of 27.5 percent; of this amount, the 
gross agricultural output value was 38.8 billion yuan, an 
increase of 5.1 percent. This year is a crucial one for 
promoting the establishment of the socialist market economy 
structure, an important year for maintaining a good economic 
development trend, and a crucial year for accelerating the 
construction of basic facilities and industries and for 
promoting Jiangxi's economy to a new level. 
  The provincial government asks the people throughout the 
province to seize the opportunity to deepen reform, to widen the 
scope of opening up, to bring about further development, to 
maintain stability, to move forward boldly with an enterprising 
spirit, to work hard and in a down-to-earth manner, to base 
themselves on agriculture, and to devote major efforts to 
industrial development so as to lay a good foundation for future 
development. 
  In his speech at the meeting, Wu Guanzheng stressed: In 
economic work, we must bring economic returns into prominence. 
People in all trades and undertakings must pay close attention 
to improving economic returns and must work out detailed 
measures and objectives. There is a need for county-level 
economic development; for developing high-yield, high-quality, 
and highly efficient agriculture; and for accurately selecting 
projects and improving economic results in the development of 
town and township enterprises. In the meantime, it is necessary 
to continue developing the individual and private economic 
sectors, as well as the foreign-invested economic sectors. In 
the course of stimulating economic development, we should handle 
correctly the relationship among reform, development, and 
stability; accelerate the establishment of the social insurance 
system; strengthen control over government officials; improve 
the comprehensive management of social order; increase the 
masses' sense of safety; and ensure increases in the peasants' 
per capita net income and increases in revenue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

