<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gansu Party Committee, Government Greet Elderly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0702141594 Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0702141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As the Spring Festival is approaching, the 
provincial party committee and government sent a letter to 
convey regards to retired cadres and elderly people throughout 
the province. The letter says: 
  Last year the province made marked achievements in reform, 
opening up, and economic construction. These achievements were 
the result of the common efforts of cadres and masses throughout 
the province, and cannot be separated from your enthusiastic 
concern and support. The letter points out: This year is a 
crucial one for the province to fulfill the Eighth Five-Year 
Plan one year ahead of schedule and to quadruple the GNP three 
years ahead of schedule. The fulfillment of this objective 
requires the efforts of cadres and masses throughout the 
province, including the concern and support of retired cadres 
and elderly people of all nationalities. They should do their 
best to display their professional skills, experience, and 
exemplary role, and should make new contributions to Gansu's 
reform and opening up, to the establishment of the socialist 
market economy structure, to economic construction, and to 
spiritual civilization. 
  The letter further points out: In this new year, we should 
make a success of the work concerning retired cadres and elderly 
people, should propagate their historic exploits and present 
devotion so as to create a fine social mood of respecting and 
loving the elderly, should show concern and care for them in 
politics and life, and should create conditions for their good 
health and longevity and for them to devote their remaining 
efforts, so that they will spend their remaining years happily. 
The letter sincerely wishes retired cadres and elderly people 
throughout the province a happy Lunar New Year and a harmonious 
family. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

