<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   New BOC President To Continue Serving Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1002014594 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 0726 GMT 
5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1002014594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By corrrespondent Dong Huifeng (5516 2585 1496) ] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 5 Feb (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--In a recent 
interview given to a ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE correspondent, Wang 
Qiren, the newly appointed president of the Bank of China, 
thanked people from different Hong Kong and Macao circles for 
their care for him, saying he missed all his Hong Kong and Macao 
friends and he had had a good time with them over the last two 
years. 
  Wang Qiren, who resigned earlier as deputy director of the 
State Council Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, said he was 
touched by the massive New Year's greeting cards and letters of 
congratulations he received from his Hong Kong and Macao 
friends. He asked the correspondent to express his regards and 
wish them all a happy new year for him. 
  He said: The important thing in dealing with Hong Kong and 
Macao compatriots is sincerity and serving them well according 
to relevant central policies in order to increase their sense of 
belonging and make them feel that we are all Chinese and Chinese 
government officials are their friends. He said many Hong Kong 
and Macao friends he came in contact with were patriotic and 
loved Hong Kong and Macao, which is the foundation for achieving 
one country, two systems, and maintaining long-term prosperity 
and stability in Hong Kong and Macao. 
  Wang Qiren pointed out that 1997 is only three years away 
and 
there are many specific tasks to do, such as actively 
propagating and popularizing the Basic Law to make it known to 
everybody, working hard to maintain the stability and prosperity 
of Hong Kong's economy, despite Britain's noncooperation, and 
various tasks for Hong Kong's transition toward 1997. This will 
turn the attention of Hong Kong and Macao compatriots to the 
motherland and make them work in concerted effort for the return 
of Hong Kong and Macao to the motherland. Only thus can we face 
the 5,000-year civilized Chinese race, history, and our 
descendants with a clear conscience. 
  In the two-and-a-half hour interview, the former State 
Council Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office deputy director said 
more than once that the Bank of China has a close relationship 
with Hong Kong and Macao; that he will continue to serve Hong 
Kong and Macao compatriots in his work and in his participation 
in the Preliminary Work Committee of the Preparatory Committee 
for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. 

</TEXT>

