<H3> <TI>   Governor Vieira Delivers Lunar New Year Message </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0902174994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1442 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, February 9 (XINHUA) -- Macao Governor 
General Vasco Joaquim Rocha Vieira said today that he is 
confident in Macao's future. 
  He said in his Lunar New Year message that in a period of 
unrest caused by different religions, races and conflicts, Macao 
is still a place which bears understanding between different 
cultures and a model in dealing with difficulties with peaceful 
attitude. 
  The governor said he is convinced that the planned visit by 
Portuguese premier and the announced visit by Portuguese 
president to the People's Republic of China would be an 
important symbol of maintenance of the mutual understanding and 
friendly cooperation between the two countries. 
  Thus, he continued, "We have sufficient reasons to predict 
that we'll have all conditions that will enable us to work for 
our economic modernization, improving our infrastructural 
construction and implementing localization policies." 
  He hoped that all people would do a good job in the new 
year, 
saying that "Our success will be a powerful contribution to the 
strengthening of friendship between China and Portugal and a 
stable base for the progress of Macao." 

</TEXT>

