<H3> <TI>   Leaders Celebrate Spring Festival </TI></H3>
<H4>   Qiao Shi in Hainan </H4>
<F P=102> OW1002130294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1237 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1002130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Haikou, February 10 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman 
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, 
today visited the construction site of the international airport 
at Sanya city, Hainan Province, south China. 
  Qiao, also member of the Standing Committee of the Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, 
expressed festival greetings to the workers and technological 
staff at the site. 
  He said that this year China is expected to make still 
greater progress in various sectors under the guidance of Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics. 
  Sanya Phoenix International Airport is one of the major 
infrastructure projects in Hainan Province. Work started in May 
1990. The airport is expected to open on July 1 this year. 
  Qiao Shi inspected the main runway and the passenger lounges 
and parking apron which are under construction. 
  He also had a talk with French specialists who are involved 
in the installation of navigational facilities. 
  From February 4 to 10, Qiao Shi, accompanied by Hainan 
Governor Ruan Chongwu, inspected Haikou, Qiongshan and Sanya 
cities, including some major projects and nature reserves. 

</TEXT>

