<F P=102> OW1002131094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1300 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1002131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Xiamen, February 10 (XINHUA) -- Liu Huaqing, 
vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, today attended 
a Spring Festival party in Xiamen city, in east China's Fujian 
Province. 
  After the meeting, Liu, also a member of the Standing 
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of 
the Chinese Communist Party, went to two ports at Xiamen to 
convey festival greetings to the on-shift workers. 
  On Wednesday, Liu visited an army unit to see officers and 
men. He talked with the soldiers and listened to them about 
their life and military training. 
  He said that at present China enjoys political stability and 
rapid and stable economic growth. 
  He urged them to seize favorable opportunities to promote 
economic construction and army construction. 
  He also called on them to study Deng Xiaoping's selected 
works, learn science and technology and improve the quality of 
the army ranks. 

