<H3> <TI>   Leaders Celebrate Spring Festival </TI></H3>
<H4>   Qian Qichen in Beijing </H4>
<F P=102> OW1002103794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1149 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1002103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Niu Changzheng 3662 7022 1767] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 3 Feb (XINHUA) -- The State Council 
Counsellor Office and the Central Research Institute of Culture 
and History held a Spring Festival tea party today in Beijing. 
Qian Qichen, member of the CPC Central Committee Political 
Bureau and vice premier of the State Council, attended today's 
tea party and extended cordial greetings to all State Council 
counselors and Central Research Institute of Culture staff on 
behalf of the State Council. 
  In his speech, Vice Premier Qian Qichen said in the 
soon-to-be-elapsed Chinese calendar year, the entire party and 
the people of all nationalities in the nation have, under the 
guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory on building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics and the party basic line, seized 
the opportunity, deepened reform, and made solid efforts in 
realizing the establishment of a socialist market economic 
system. In the past year, China achieved rapid economic growth; 
the market thrived; the standard of living level improved; 
society enjoyed stability; people of all nationalities showed 
solidarity; various social undertakings achieved new progress; 
the anticorruption struggle led by the CPC Central Committee and 
the State Council, which won the hearts and minds of the people, 
scored initial results; diplomatic work showed marked results, 
creating a more advantageous international environment for our 
country's economic construction. We are also pleased to know 
that the multiparty cooperation and political consultative 
system, under CPC leadership, has been further consolidated and 
that the party's united front work has been constantly 
strengthened. Members of the Communist Party and various 
democratic parties and patriots without party affiliation 
showing utter devotion to one other, sharing weal and woe, and 
joining in discussing national affairs have become an important 
feature in building socialism with Chinese characteristics. 
  The coming Chinese new year will be particularly crucial for 
building our country's socialist market economy as a number of 
major reform measures will be introduced that year. It is 
necessary to continuously give play to the political superiority 
of the united front work in the new period, to mobilize all 
positive factors, seize the opportunity, deepen reform, open up 
wider, and accelerate the pace of building the socialist market 
economic system. 
  Qian Qichen said that in the past year, the state counselors 
conducted a massive number of investigations and 
enthusiastically advanced proposals on government work, to which 
leading comrades of the CPC Central Committee, the State 
Council, and relevant departments attached great importance. 
Central Research Institute of Culture and History staff members 
worked diligently and achieved marked results in various social 
and cultural undertakings. In addition, Central Research 
Institute of Culture and History counselors and staff members 
also established ties with various overseas circles, forged 
friendships with them, and contributed to economic and cultural 
exchanges between China and overseas areas and to the great 
cause of reunification. 
  At the tea party, State Council Counselors Office and 
Central 
Research Institute of Culture and History representatives 
reviewed their work in the past year and expressed their wishes 
to continue contributing to socialist modernization construction 
and to the building of spiritual and material civilizations with 
their knowledge and special skills. 
  Other leading comrades who attended today's tea party 
included: Cheng Siyuan, vice chairman of the National People's 
Congress Standing Committee; Luo Gan, state councillor and 
secretary general of the State Council; and Hu Sheng, vice 
chairman of the national committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference. 
  Wan Shaofen, deputy head of the CPC Central Committee United 
Front Work Department, presided over today's tea party. 
  Responsible people from the relevant CPC Central Committee 
and State Council departments as well as dozens of Central 
Research Institute of Culture and History counselors and staff 
members attended today's tea party. 

</TEXT>

