<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Zheng Qingdong (6774 1987 2639)] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 9 Feb (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan and Hu 
Jintao, members of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau 
Standing Committee, called on Comrades Song Ping, Bo Yibo, and 
Song Renqiong on the morning of 7 February to extend Spring 
Festival greetings and cordial regards to them on behalf of the 
CPC Central Committee and the State Council. 
  Li Ruihuan and Hu Jintao warmly inquired about the living 
and 
health conditions of the three veteran comrades, briefed them on 
the current domestic situation and the basic principle for work 
in 1994, and also expressed the hope that the veteran comrades 
will make more suggestions concerning the work of the party 
Central Committee and the State Council so as to help the 
central authorities do their work well. 
  After asking Li Ruihuan and Hu Jintao to convey their thanks 
and New Year's greetings to leading comrades of the CPC Central 
Committee and the State Council, Song Ping, Bo Yibo, and Song 
Renqiong said: Since the Third Plenary Session of the 11th CPC 
Central Committee, the situation in our country has been 
improving day by day. Its economy has been growing rapidly; its 
overall strength has expanded somewhat, and the people's living 
standards have improved to some extent. We must further 
emancipate our minds, seek truth from facts, continue to advance 
along the road of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics, strive to advance to a new level, and strive to 
fulfill the second-step strategic objective ahead of schedule to 
win still greater victories! 
  Those who accompanied Li Ruihuan and Hu Jintao to call on 
the 
veteran comrades also included Zeng Qinghong, director of the 
CPC Central Committee General Office, and Lu Feng, director of 
the CPC Central Committee Organizational Department. 

</TEXT>

