<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hu Ping Inspects Shenzhen SEZ </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0902112094 Hong Kong WEN WEI PO in Chinese 7 Feb 94 p A2 </F>
<F P=103> HK0902112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong WEN WEI PO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report: "Hu Ping Inspects Shenzhen"] </F>
  [Text] According to news from Shenzhen, Hu Ping, director 
of the State Council's Special Economic Zones [SEZ] Office, 
inspected Shenzhen from 3 to 6 February. He pointed out: 
Shenzhen has scored achievements through solid work and it 
should still rely on solid work to have a more leading edge. 
Travelling with a minimum of pomp, Hu Ping and his five-member 
party, inspected the city's goods and material corporation, 
urban construction group, petrochemical group, Yantian port, 
Shatoujiao, and Futian Bonded Area; heard work reports by 
Shenzhen Mayor Li Youwei and Vice Mayor Wang Zhongfu; and 
inquired in detail about the measures adopted by Shenzhen in 
opening wider to the outside world and deepening reform. Hu 
Ping and his party left Shenzhen today. 

</TEXT>

