<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Protests Taiwan Leader's Southeast Asia Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1202082294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0753 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1202082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 12 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese Foreign 
Ministry today lodged a protest to the Indonesian and Philippine 
envoys here against the two countries allowing visit and 
stopover by "high-ranking officials" from Taiwan, including Li 
Teng-hui. 
  On February 9, Li and other "high-ranking officials" from 
Taiwan arrived at Bali island of Indonesia for a "vacational 
visit" and on February 11, Indonesian President Suharto met with 
Li on the island, according to sources of the Foreign Ministry. 
  On his way to Indonesia, Li stopped over at Subic and met 
with Philippine President Fidel Ramos, the sources said. 

</TEXT>

